00:22:24.410 --> 00:22:26.000
in it and that labour market will change.

00:22:26.200 --> 00:22:32.790
There must be a safety net for the public sector
with educational services in order for people

00:22:32.990 --> 00:22:40.110
to be retrained, or to be able to acquire other
professions and find employment in that labor market.

00:22:40.310 --> 00:22:44.630
The public sector is not sufficiently
prepared for this role.

00:22:44.830 --> 00:22:54.200
Not ready because those schools would not care,
but there is not an assignment that would say

00:22:54.400 --> 00:22:59.650
how the institutions should do it.

00:22:59.850 --> 00:23:07.500
And they primarily do not feel this need.
Because support for education is directed

00:23:07.700 --> 00:23:13.020
a bit outside the education sector
and revolves around the employment office.

00:23:13.220 --> 00:23:16.300
Or around the own initiative
of large companies that are already working

00:23:16.500 --> 00:23:18.550
on further training of employees.

00:23:19.700 --> 00:23:22.350
The primary role in this should be
played by those schools,

00:23:22.550 --> 00:23:25.010
support and assignments should come.

00:23:25.210 --> 00:23:29.900
Support in terms of finance and in terms
of defining what we want and what new roles

00:23:30.100 --> 00:23:36.000
these institutions should play. What should high
schools and colleges do in the new reality.

00:23:38.600 --> 00:23:45.380
And sharing the impact of the new, dynamic
economy that awaits us in the coming months.

00:23:45.580 --> 00:23:52.820
We have been slapped, now we are still
in the mode of economic subsidies,

00:23:53.020 --> 00:23:57.840
but in time they will end
and some sectors will fall to the bottom

00:23:58.040 --> 00:24:01.200
and it will be necessary to continue
working with those employees.

00:24:01.400 --> 00:24:12.300
Public support will be need to be provided
so that these employees can find employment somewhere.

00:24:13.700 --> 00:24:16.160
That is the basic point,
I can bring to this debate.

00:24:16.360 --> 00:24:21.450
Thank you so much for this point.

00:24:21.650 --> 00:24:25.400
Again, I would like to invite the participants
of the discussion to write us comments

00:24:25.600 --> 00:24:29.400
and questions so that we can answer them.

00:24:29.600 --> 00:24:32.450
I have the first questions from the audience.

00:24:38.500 --> 00:24:42.350
The question is about pouring liquidity
into the economy.

00:24:44.550 --> 00:24:48.180
Economists have strongly appealed to
the government,

00:24:48.380 --> 00:24:53.000
as whole economical sectors were being closed,

00:24:53.200 --> 00:25:03.000
to immediately release liquidity,
to pump money into the economy,

00:25:03.200 --> 00:25:11.960
and our viewers would like to know
how long we can work this way,

00:25:12.160 --> 00:25:18.100
how long it can last us,
let's say this pouring money into the economy.

00:25:18.300 --> 00:25:22.650
This is definitely a question for
our two economists in the panel,

00:25:22.850 --> 00:25:26.700
I do not know if
Mrs Nerudova would like to start?

00:25:28.500 --> 00:25:32.999
Thank you, I read that it was a question
aimed at me.

00:25:33.199 --> 00:25:40.200
I think it's necessary to realize, and
I must say I have goosebumps, when someone

00:25:40.400 --> 00:25:45.120
says the word "pump",
because there was no pumping in our country.

00:25:45.320 --> 00:25:48.000
It is necessary to realize that
in comparison with other states

00:25:48.200 --> 00:25:49.650
there has been no pumping,

00:25:49.850 --> 00:25:55.500
I want to say, that all things are related.

00:25:55.700 --> 00:25:58.345
At the beginning of the spring crisis,
when was the lockdown,

00:25:58.545 --> 00:26:04.000
we said that liquidity needs to be brought
into the economy,.

00:26:04.200 --> 00:26:10.200
We pointed out that the state has
relatively simple, effective and cheap tools

00:26:10.400 --> 00:26:12.600
to get liquidity into the economy.

00:26:12.800 --> 00:26:18.000
I must say that we were basically
not heard at all, because we proposed that

00:26:18.200 --> 00:26:24.800
for example, to abolish the payment of VAT,
which is a very effective tool.

00:26:25.000 --> 00:26:32.000
It was a really big slap in the spring,
so we wre talking about the waivering of

00:26:32.200 --> 00:26:37.350
social and health insurence payments for employers.

00:26:37.550 --> 00:26:44.300
I must say that the spring crisis has shown
that there is essentially zero state

00:26:44.500 --> 00:26:47.650
confidence in businesses in the economy,
because unlike Western countries,

00:26:47.850 --> 00:26:52.275
which trusted entrepreneurs and
really tried to help them effectively

00:26:52.475 --> 00:26:59.050
we have created incredibly complex
administrative tools that a lot of entrepreneurs

00:26:59.250 --> 00:27:03.650
didn't get the help at all, or they got it
late, or they said to themselves

00:27:03.850 --> 00:27:06.200
"it's not worth it, I'll help myself".

00:27:06.400 --> 00:27:12.550
So, from my point of view in the spring,
the help came very late and the fact

00:27:12.750 --> 00:27:15.850
that it came late was due to the fact
that there was simply no trust

00:27:16.050 --> 00:27:20.770
n the business sector and we still did not
believe that entrepreneurs needed help

00:27:20.970 --> 00:27:24.250
and the state felt more like
the help would be misused.

00:27:24.450 --> 00:27:30.800
So the excessive administrative burden
basically caused that the aid was ineffective.

00:27:31.000 --> 00:27:41.250
Then, when the economy defrosted and restarted,
the right manager should have

00:27:41.450 --> 00:27:48.000
evaluated these tools,
their effectiveness and impacts.

00:27:48.200 --> 00:27:51.230
I have to say,
that unfortunately this did not happen.

00:27:54.430 --> 00:28:00.100
The second wave came and we pulled the tools
out of the hat again, thinking they worked.

00:28:00.300 --> 00:28:04.999
Yes, and at least they were
set up in time at the moment,

00:28:05.199 --> 00:28:08.400
but because they already existed
so they just were recovered,

00:28:08.600 --> 00:28:14.800
but we do not know if they were effective,
so maybe we can do something what is not effective,

00:28:15.000 --> 00:28:20.500
from my point of view is certainly not effective
to help with 500CZK a day to self-employed person,

00:28:20.700 --> 00:28:25.500
who for example rents a hairdressing salon
and monthly rents cost 20 000 CZK,

00:28:25.700 --> 00:28:30.000
so this help is really not effective
because it does not even cover fixed costs.

00:28:30.200 --> 00:28:35.800
And here it is necessary to say, just for
comparison, how the aid looks like west of us,

00:28:35.796 --> 00:28:41.636
so small and medium-sized enterprises
in Germany at this moment have

00:28:41.836 --> 00:28:48.400
aid that will receive 70 percent of the
turnover from November 2019.

00:28:48.600 --> 00:28:53.620
If restaurants in Germany are closed
till January 10, they will receive

00:28:53.820 --> 00:29:00.650
70 percent of their turnover in December 2019
as an aid in December 2020.

00:29:00.850 --> 00:29:06.000
So you feel from these numbers that the
word pumped can definitely not be used,

00:29:06.030 --> 00:29:07.450
because the Germans are pumping,

00:29:07.650 --> 00:29:13.350
in our country, there is definitely
no pumping of help for entrepreneurs

00:29:13.550 --> 00:29:21.200
And the question of how long,
the state should do everything to prevent

00:29:21.400 --> 00:29:23.700
the economy from closing for the third time,

00:29:23.900 --> 00:29:27.430
but I'm afraid that just as
the train missed us in the summer,

00:29:27.630 --> 00:29:29.480
the train again missed us at the moment

00:29:29.680 --> 00:29:35.200
because the countries around us who
knew they have to build trace capacity,

00:29:35.400 --> 00:29:39.370
that they had to build call centers
and testing capacity,

00:29:39.570 --> 00:29:43.800
so today they know that whoeve
r inoculates the first, largest population

00:29:44.000 --> 00:29:48.550
will be able to start economy
and will have no more losses .

00:29:48.750 --> 00:29:54.700
This is not happening here
and we are preparing for third wave.

00:29:54.900 --> 00:29:59.650
And I call it the third, stupid lockdown,
because that lockdown might not be at all.

00:29:59.850 --> 00:30:04.450
If we were to building vaccination centers
at this moment, as they do in Germany,

00:30:04.650 --> 00:30:07.400
so that the economic damages
would be as small as possible.

00:30:07.600 --> 00:30:11.180
So how long can it take?
Well, we will probably survive the third wave,

00:30:11.380 --> 00:30:15.750
but we will have a huge deficit, we will
have huge costs of servicing the state debt,

00:30:15.950 --> 00:30:24.500
we will have a large debt,
if we get to 60 percent of GDP of total debt,

00:30:24.700 --> 00:30:29.500
then it must be said, that this debt will
definitely not be reduced by cutting expenditures.

00:30:29.700 --> 00:30:32.600
Truth needs to be told to the citizens.
if there will be a third wave

00:30:32.800 --> 00:30:38.000
and we will have such a large debt,
so cutting expenditures will not change that.

00:30:38.200 --> 00:30:43.000
And there will come a time when we will have
to raise taxes and all of us will pay it.

00:30:43.200 --> 00:30:48.000
And among us, abolition of the super-gross
wage and that debt over 130 billion CZK

00:30:48.200 --> 00:30:50.700
all of us will pay it as well

00:30:50.900 --> 00:30:55.500
Just to be clear, it says it helps,
it doesn't help.

00:30:55.700 --> 00:30:58.250
Two-thirds of what is proposed
will go to high incomers

00:30:58.450 --> 00:31:00.740
but we all will pay the debt,
in the form of higher taxes.

00:31:00.940 --> 00:31:06.000
So much for me,
I hope I somehow left room for Helena,

00:31:06.200 --> 00:31:10.100
That I did not say all of it.

00:31:10.300 --> 00:31:14.900
Thank you very much, Mrs. Horská,
do you want to add something directly to this,

00:31:15.009 --> 00:31:22.009
or do you think all important things
about pumping money into the economy,

00:31:22.209 --> 00:31:24.400
which did not happen, were said here?

00:31:24.600 --> 00:31:31.260
I think Dana was exhausting and emotional
at the same time, because she's right.

00:31:31.460 --> 00:31:36.980
When we compare and promises versus actions,
I'm not surprised that those emotions

00:31:37.180 --> 00:31:42.300
are so bubbling, because just the numbers,
I really like numbers,

00:31:42.500 --> 00:31:45.800
so I'll start with the numbers again,
and I'll probably stay with them,

00:31:46.000 --> 00:31:48.988
because Dana said everything needed,

00:31:49.188 --> 00:31:54.600
and the figures are such that aid was paid
to this economy at the end of November,

00:31:54.800 --> 00:32:01.000
not counting the purchase of Chinese respirators
and the rescue of indebted hospitals

00:32:01.200 --> 00:32:05.450
unrelated to the covid and many other
expenses unrelated to the covid,

00:32:05.650 --> 00:32:10.550
so the aid was also calculated
by the Ministry of Finance at 166 billion CZK,

00:32:10.750 --> 00:32:17.100
that is 55% of the promised aid
in the amount of 289 billion CZK

00:32:17.300 --> 00:32:22.200
and those loans which were promised
in the amount of almost 800 billions CZK

00:32:22.400 --> 00:32:24.550
are drawn in units of percent.

00:32:24.750 --> 00:32:29.000
because the companies, when they needed
help at the most critical time,

00:32:29.200 --> 00:32:35.250
as Danuše mentioned, in the spring, did not
really get the help and they helped themselves.

00:32:35.450 --> 00:32:41.400
At the moment when the various covid programs
such Covic Plus, Covid EGAP, Covid Export...

00:32:41.600 --> 00:32:48.200
were already up and running, which was
very late, actually at the end of the first wave,

00:32:48.400 --> 00:32:49.450
so the companies said

00:32:49.445 --> 00:32:53.920
"Ok somehow we managed it,
somehow we helped ourselves and it goes on"

00:32:53.921 --> 00:33:01.200
Perhaps what I would add to Danuše is that
the actually paid out aid was significantly lower,

00:33:01.400 --> 00:33:03.400
I would agree that it was ineffective

00:33:03.600 --> 00:33:10.200
and also it freezes, as Mr Gargulák
was talking about,

00:33:10.400 --> 00:33:14.650
it freezes the strucure of economy,
that outdated structure of the economy,

00:33:14.850 --> 00:33:22.555
it means that it creates in our employees
and employers, ie companies, the feeling,

00:33:22.755 --> 00:33:26.700
that nothing will actually changed
and nothing has changed

00:33:26.900 --> 00:33:36.000
and that we will then wake up to the original
reality and we start working in those

00:33:36.200 --> 00:33:41.000
original works with original knowledge
and skills.

00:33:41.200 --> 00:33:44.800
And we will suffice until the end of our working life

00:33:45.000 --> 00:33:49.000
Unfortunately, the reality is really different,
because as it was said here before

00:33:49.200 --> 00:33:54.300
and we should repeat it so that it gets stuck
in people's memory, there is acceleration here.

00:33:54.500 --> 00:33:58.240
There is an acceleration of changes
and it requires a great challenge

00:33:58.440 --> 00:34:02.440
for employees, employers and the government.

00:34:02.640 --> 00:34:08.340
And it is a question of digitization:
being able to adapt for employees,

00:34:08.540 --> 00:34:11.110
now we can see a change in working regime,

00:34:11.310 --> 00:34:16.000
for companies a change in
work organization, new business models,

00:34:16.200 --> 00:34:18.470
a new functioning of the economy

00:34:18.670 --> 00:34:23.500
and we have a state here that
instead of reducing risk and uncertainty,

00:34:23.700 --> 00:34:31.000
It is first week of December and
we do not know yet, what taxes,

00:34:31.200 --> 00:34:34.000
we will pay from the first month
of the following year.

00:34:34.200 --> 00:34:38.880
We don't know what the conditions of the covid
would look like if another wave came

00:34:39.080 --> 00:34:41.000
We don't even know
what next week will look like.

00:34:41.200 --> 00:34:48.850
So these are the challenges we face.
Without flexibility, ability to improvise,

00:34:49.050 --> 00:34:53.950
our ability to improvise is amazing,
but I have a feeling that the government

00:34:54.150 --> 00:34:57.300
is abusing it too much
and relying too much on it,

00:34:57.500 --> 00:35:03.210
so unfortunately it doesn't look very good,
but we've done worse, we can do this,

00:35:03.229 --> 00:35:08.000
but we can miss the train and I don't think
we should, it would be a great pity.

00:35:08.200 --> 00:35:14.400
Thank you, I don't know if you saw,
but Mr. Peksa was smiling next to me

00:35:14.600 --> 00:35:21.470
when you were speaking, so I she would like
to ask, if he wants to add something.

00:35:23.000 --> 00:35:28.310
I certainly agree, because, as has been said,
the aid was very ineffective,

00:35:28.510 --> 00:35:40.600
Fortunately, during this crisis, the European
response was more sensible than in the past.

00:35:40.800 --> 00:35:45.800
Because most governments have understood
what to do, which means that given

00:35:45.796 --> 00:35:50.400
the interconnectedness of the economy within
the common market, we have been partly saved

00:35:50.600 --> 00:35:55.800
because the others around us have behaved sensibly.
For example, the Germans.

00:35:56.000 --> 00:35:59.900
Because if they did it as badly
as our government did,

00:36:00.100 --> 00:36:03.170
we were in worse trouble than we are now.

00:36:07.370 --> 00:36:09.800
Perhaps I would add a side note,

00:36:14.000 --> 00:36:23.950
I think that the answer at the level of the
European Economic Area, was spontaneous,

00:36:24.150 --> 00:36:28.750
but was sensible,
but it was not coordinated in any way.

00:36:28.950 --> 00:36:31.800
As the Member States have been arguing
about what they will do,

00:36:32.000 --> 00:36:34.890
will do some rescue package,
and if they approve it at all,

00:36:35.090 --> 00:36:38.700
so the whole process is not going effectively.

00:36:38.900 --> 00:36:44.000
We do not yet know whether we will have a budget
or whether Hungary will block

00:36:44.200 --> 00:36:47.890
it for some internal Hungarian reasons.

00:36:48.090 --> 00:36:53.950
This is quite sad in my view, and we
should look for a way to make the management

00:36:54.150 --> 00:37:01.400
of the whole European economy work more
rationally, because as it is set up now,

00:37:01.600 --> 00:37:03.880
it is cumbersome and inefficient.

00:37:04.080 --> 00:37:07.570
Thank you very much,
I have another question from the audience.

00:37:07.770 --> 00:37:16.600
,I would like to ask Mrs Homfray about
employment.

00:37:16.800 --> 00:37:24.750
The question is, in the sense of whether
the financial evaluation of the functions

00:37:24.950 --> 00:37:34.450
using home office or flexible hours,
that came with quarantine economy, will decrease.

00:37:39.000 --> 00:37:42.000
Mrs Homfray, can you comment on this,

00:37:42.200 --> 00:37:52.000
do you think that there is room for a change
in financial valuation in these sectors?

00:37:52.200 --> 00:37:58.270
To be honest, I hope not.
I would not like someone's salary to be reduced

00:37:58.470 --> 00:38:01.100
because they can work in the evening.

00:38:01.300 --> 00:38:07.500
Nor do I think that this should necessarily
be a reason for a reward preference.

00:38:07.700 --> 00:38:13.750
Frankly, what I hope is that whether
flexible working hours or a home office

00:38:13.950 --> 00:38:17.150
will finally stop being taken as a benefit,
because that is not a benefit.

00:38:17.350 --> 00:38:21.250
It is an alternative work arrangement that
has its advantages and disadvantages

00:38:21.450 --> 00:38:27.000
for both parties and at the same time
for each and every employee it does not have

00:38:27.200 --> 00:38:28.460
the same advantages and disadvantages.

00:38:28.660 --> 00:38:34.150
So definitely take it as a benefit,
especially the home office,

00:38:34.350 --> 00:38:39.000
it was really taken that way until the spring,
for a number of employers or the vast majority.

00:38:39.200 --> 00:38:45.120
Take it as a benefit, which like the icing
on the cake, I will allow someone to do it

00:38:45.320 --> 00:38:50.000
he will reward me for it simply with
uncontrolled and immense flexibility,

00:38:50.200 --> 00:38:52.150
so that by chance someone does not think
he does not work at home,

00:38:52.350 --> 00:38:55.100
so I firmly believe that after this
year's experience

00:38:55.300 --> 00:38:57.510
with this perception could and should be over.

00:38:57.710 --> 00:39:02.430
Whether this will have any impact on
remuneration or on the growth

00:39:02.630 --> 00:39:13.622
or decline of specific wages for a certain
type of job, just time will tell.

00:39:14.300 --> 00:39:18.700
But there will be many more factors
that will now play a role in the growth

00:39:18.900 --> 00:39:21.800
or decline of wage levels in
individual professions.

00:39:22.000 --> 00:39:24.440
We simply have segments of the labor market here,

00:39:24.640 --> 00:39:29.000
where it already seems, such as the hotel
and tourism industry,

00:39:29.200 --> 00:39:33.850
that it may or already disappeared
up to 50% of jobs.

00:39:34.050 --> 00:39:39.000
and these people will get somewhere
onto some empty labor market,

00:39:39.200 --> 00:39:42.100
They will be theoretically qualified
in some other fields.

00:39:42.300 --> 00:39:53.000
So certainly the wage level will not be
influenced only by that flexible arrangement.

00:39:53.200 --> 00:40:01.300
I see that the interviewer asked if
the benefit would working from the office.

00:40:01.500 --> 00:40:08.500
It's also not a benefit, but honestly it is,
because the experience is not unequivocally

00:40:08.700 --> 00:40:12.500
positive, as we are not prepared for it,
we were not prepared,

00:40:12.700 --> 00:40:16.000
nor for the employers,
as it follows from those surveys,

00:40:16.200 --> 00:40:20.400
and honestly for me it is no surprise,
because various researches,

00:40:20.600 --> 00:40:22.650
for example from Germany, where they have
more experience with home office and

00:40:22.850 --> 00:40:28.640
and other flexible forms,
have shown that people miss those offices.

00:40:28.840 --> 00:40:35.475
They miss their colleagues,
they miss informal faster work matters,

00:40:35.675 --> 00:40:42.180
you really don't transfer everything to ZOOM
and other similar platforms.

00:40:42.380 --> 00:40:48.460
And isolation plays a role,
domestic factors play a role,

00:40:48.660 --> 00:40:55.600
so I think the experience will be such that
and again I say the experience is new to us

00:40:55.800 --> 00:41:00.300
but abroad they have already figured out
that the home office is nice,

