We keep talking about the Czech economy being
dependent on the automotive industry,

00:48:30.940 --> 00:48:33.800
and rarely talking about it in the Czech
economy,

00:48:34.000 --> 00:48:37.400
digital economy already makes 8 percent of GDP

00:48:37.600 --> 00:48:42.350
and has a tremendous potential to rise,
because during covid, and here again

00:48:42.550 --> 00:48:49.090
I begin to use data from the McKinsey study
which was recently published, about Digital Challenges

00:48:49.290 --> 00:48:52.600
and it shows that during the covid
in Central and Eastern Europe

00:48:52.800 --> 00:48:57.000
there the rate of digitization of those
economies has risen by 50%

00:48:57.200 --> 00:48:59.250
that amount of users increased significantly,

00:48:59.450 --> 00:49:03.800
there has been an acceleration
in the number of clients using online,

00:49:04.000 --> 00:49:08.200
for example 7 out of 10 Czechs
are using online shops.

00:49:08.400 --> 00:49:13.200
It is people who did not even think
before about ordering food online

00:49:13.400 --> 00:49:16.000
digitally and they are
using these services now.

00:49:16.200 --> 00:49:20.000
And most of them are going to
use this new skill further,

00:49:20.200 --> 00:49:23.300
that means, we are actually educating people.

00:49:23.500 --> 00:49:29.250
It shows that the Digital as such has
huge potential for growth,

00:49:29.450 --> 00:49:32.000
but we throw sticks under our feet.

00:49:32.200 --> 00:49:35.500
And this is exactly the non-digitized
state administration,

00:49:35.700 --> 00:49:39.400
the inability of the state
administration to work with data,

00:49:39.600 --> 00:49:44.400
meaning, to be able to collect data, to
structure data, to use them,

00:49:44.600 --> 00:49:47.500
to make decisions on the basis of data,

00:49:47.700 --> 00:49:51.400
but in every section in which
the state administration works

00:49:51.600 --> 00:49:53.400
we always come across a problem.

00:49:53.600 --> 00:49:57.900
From the collection of data to their analysis,
to their aggregation,

00:49:58.100 --> 00:50:02.000
to their processing and
to their decision-making based on data,

00:50:02.200 --> 00:50:06.000
because it became clear during the covid,
that our government was not able to

00:50:06.200 --> 00:50:09.200
to make decisions at all,
or was not willing to make decisions

00:50:09.400 --> 00:50:17.250
So we have great potential.
And just for the digitization,

00:50:17.450 --> 00:50:20.220
I see that Danuše is asking for word,
so I will let her speak,

00:50:20.420 --> 00:50:27.730
During the covid some sectors rapidly
moved towards digitalization,

00:50:27.930 --> 00:50:31.200
It will probably not surprise you
but it was, of course, retail,

00:50:31.400 --> 00:50:38.220
but it is also banking and if I recall correctly,
it was also telecommunications services.

00:50:38.420 --> 00:50:42.000
On the contrary, who was the least digitized,
and I was quite surprised,

00:50:42.200 --> 00:50:48.200
were the travel agencies, which is very
surprising given what they experienced,

00:50:48.341 --> 00:50:51.560
but also the government
and insurance companies.

00:50:51.562 --> 00:50:56.150
So we see that, each of the sectors reacts
differently to these covid shocks.

00:50:56.350 --> 00:51:03.250
Taken together, there is great potential
to actually use the covid shock

00:51:03.450 --> 00:51:07.500
to accelerate digitization,
but we must have prepared

00:51:07.700 --> 00:51:11.600
infrastructure, institutions
including the government,

00:51:11.800 --> 00:51:17.350
high-quality Internet connection,
and especially the prepared population,

00:51:17.550 --> 00:51:21.000
employees, the workforce.
They must be prepared for the challenges

00:51:21.200 --> 00:51:24.560
that await us, because we will
probably not do the same work

00:51:24.760 --> 00:51:30.000
for the rest of our lives
and we will have to adapt to new challenges

00:51:30.200 --> 00:51:34.300
and we will have to change occupations,
we will have to change our work skills.

00:51:34.500 --> 00:51:37.330
So that is my comments,
thank you for the word.

